The paper discusses the development of algorithms and software for simulation of power systems, which involves numerical analysis and computation. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), which deals with the analysis and control of complex systems. The paper also discusses the impact of integration time step on convergence, which is related to numerical analysis and computation, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the simulation of transmission and distribution systems, which are related to power systems, making cs.PF (Power and Energy) another likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of co-simulation techniques, which involves the integration of different systems, making cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the validation of the proposed methods against commercial software, which involves the comparison of different simulation results, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) another likely sub-category.
